Retention and Security of Personal Data
Personal information that Userguiding processes on behalf of its Customers as a processor is retained for the period set forth in the Data Processing Agreement between UserGuiding and its Customers unless Userguiding is required to retain the Personal Data for a longer period to comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our legal agreements and policies.
We have implemented commercially reasonable technical, organizational, and security measures designed to protect your data. However, please note that we cannot guarantee that the information will not be compromised as a result of unauthorized penetration to our servers.
Transfers of personal data
Personal data collected by us is securely stored on Amazon Web Services (AWS) servers located in the European Union and the United States. For international data transfers, we rely on Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) to ensure compliance with applicable regulations. Customers subscribed to our Pro Plan have the flexibility to select their preferred data residency, choosing between EU or US data centers to align with their specific governance requirements. Additionally, if your organization requires tailored data residency options to meet strict data governance frameworks, we can accommodate those needs. For transfers of personal data outside the EU/EEA, we ensure that recipients commit to robust contractual agreements to safeguard your data.
In addition to the third parties mentioned above, we may share your data as follows: (i) with courts or competent authorities, to comply with applicable laws, regulations, and requests of law enforcement; (ii) in case we sell or transfer, or we consider selling or transferring, some or all of our business, shares or assets to a third party; (iii) if we are acquired by, or merged with, a third party entity, or in the event of bankruptcy; (iv) where you have provided your consent to us sharing or transferring your data.
The EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework (EU-U.S. DPF), the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework (UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF)
If you are a resident of the EEA or the UK, we will protect your data when it is transferred outside of the EEA and the UK by processing it in a territory that the European Commission has determined provides an adequate level of protection for personal data; or otherwise ensuring appropriate safeguards are in place to protect your personal data. For transfers of your data to:
UserGuiding is based in the US, we rely on the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework (“EU-U.S. DPF”), and the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF (“UK-U.S. DPF”) as set forth by the U.S. Department of Commerce. To learn more about the Data Privacy Framework (“DPF”) program, and to view our certification, please visit
https://www.dataprivacyframework.gov/
;
recipients who are located outside of the EEA or the UK, we rely on the EU-U.S. DPF or UK-U.S. DPF-U.S. DPF where those recipients are located in the US or for onward transfers from the US, and otherwise we rely on the EU Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) or the UK International Data Transfer Agreement (IDTA).
UserGuiding complies with the EU-U.S. DPF, and the UK-U.S. DPF as set forth by the U.S. Department of Commerce.  Imagine Privacy, Inc. has certified to the U.S. Department of Commerce that it adheres to (i) the EU-U.S. DPF Principles concerning the processing of personal data received from the European Union in reliance on the EU-U.S. DPF and from the United Kingdom in reliance on the UK-U.S. DPF. If there is any conflict between the terms in this privacy policy and the EU-U.S. DPF Principles DPF Principles, the Principles shall govern.  To learn more about the DPF program, and to view our certification, please visit
https://www.dataprivacyframework.gov/
.
In compliance with the EU-U.S. DPF, the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF, UserGuiding commits to resolve DPF Principles-related complaints about our collection and use of your Personal Information. EU and UK individuals with inquiries or complaints regarding our handling of Personal Information received in reliance on the EU-U.S. DPF, and/or the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF should first contact UserGuiding through our
privacy@userguiding.com
In compliance with the EU-U.S. DPF and the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF, UserGuiding commits to cooperate and comply respectively with the advice of the panel established by the EU data protection authorities (“DPAs“), the UK Information Commissioner’s Office (ICO) with regard to unresolved complaints concerning our handling of personal data received in reliance on the EU-U.S. DPF and the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF. Under certain conditions, it may be possible to invoke binding arbitration for complaints regarding DPF compliance not resolved by any of the other DPF mechanisms, see here for additional information.
UserGuiding remains responsible if its service provider, when acting on its behalf, processes personal data in a manner inconsistent with the DPF Principles, unless it is not responsible for the event giving rise to the damage.
The Federal Trade Commission has jurisdiction over UserGuiding’s compliance with the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework EU-U.S. DPF, the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF.
Californian Residents Privacy Notice Section
The following section applies specifically to the personal data of California residents, as defined by the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA).
Processing Californian Personal Data
UserGuiding acts as a Service Provider under the CCPA when processing Californian Personal Data. We process such data strictly to perform the SaaS Agreement ("
Business Purpose
") or as otherwise permitted by the CCPA.
As a Service Provider, we certify that:
(i) We
will not sell or share
Californian Personal Data.
(ii) We
will not process Californian Personal Data outside the direct business relationship between UserGuiding and its customers
, except as required by applicable law.
(iii) We will
not combine Californian Personal Data with data collected from other sources unless it is received in connection
with our obligations under the SaaS Agreement.
Compliance with CCPA Obligations
UserGuiding complies with all requirements applicable to a Service Provider under the CCPA, ensuring the same level of privacy protection required by the law. If we determine that we are unable to meet our obligations under the CCPA, we will promptly notify our customers.
We may retain, use, or disclose
Californian Personal Data
solely for the following purposes:
(i) Retaining and employing another Service Provider as a subcontractor, provided the subcontractor also meets the requirements of a Service Provider under the CCPA.
(ii) Detecting data security incidents or protecting against fraudulent or illegal activity.
(iii) Complying with federal, state, or local laws.
(iv) Responding to civil, criminal, or regulatory inquiries, investigations, subpoenas, or summons from federal, state, or local authorities.
(v) Cooperating with law enforcement agencies regarding activities that we reasonably and in good faith believe may violate laws.
(vi) Exercising or defending legal claims.
Ensuring Ongoing CCPA Compliance
Our customers may take reasonable and appropriate steps to verify that UserGuiding is processing Californian Personal Data by CCPA requirements and may act to stop and remediate any unauthorized use of such data. UserGuiding and its customers acknowledge and agree that the disclosure of Californian Personal Data by our customers to UserGuiding does not constitute monetary or other valuable consideration exchanged between the parties.
For more details about your rights under the CCPA and how UserGuiding processes personal data, please contact us at
privacy@userguiding.com
.
